abstract: The legal opinions were written during previous Democratic and Republican administrations by the Justice Department’s Office of Legal Counsel.
snippet: The legal opinions were written during previous Democratic and Republican administrations by the Justice Department’s Office of Legal Counsel.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Justice Department has released several internal legal opinions that could help bolster President Trump’s claim of executive privilege in barring Congress from interviewing witnesses and collecting documents from the executive branch.

abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Friday, Dec. 13, 2019.
snippet: Corrections that appeared in print on Friday, Dec. 13, 2019.
lead_paragraph: An article on Thursday about the political climate in Britain amid the election campaign  misstated the age of Queen Elizabeth II. She is 93 years old, not 95.

abstract: Quotation of the Day for Friday, December 13, 2019.
snippet: Quotation of the Day for Friday, December 13, 2019.
lead_paragraph: “I’m a big believer that if you stifle a protest, it’s not going to stifle the protest.”
headline_main: Quotation of the Day: Unease at Trump’s Order to Tackle Anti-Semitism

abstract: Voters pick whichever candidate exhausts them less.
snippet: Voters pick whichever candidate exhausts them less.
lead_paragraph: There are two power blocs driving politics today. First, there’s the proletariat. These are the working-class voters who go to Trump rallies in the U.S. and powered Brexit and Boris Johnson’s campaign in the U.K. They see their best world receding and they want a tough guy to bring it back.

abstract: U.S. asylum seekers sent to Guatemala under a new Trump administration program have mostly preferred to return to their country of origin instead of staying in the Central American nation, Guatemala's Interior Minister said on Thursday.
snippet: U.S. asylum seekers sent to Guatemala under a new Trump administration program have mostly preferred to return to their country of origin instead of staying in the Central American nation, Guatemala's Interior Minister said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: GUATEMALA CITY — U.S. asylum seekers sent to Guatemala under a new Trump administration program have mostly preferred to return to their country of origin instead of staying in the Central American nation, Guatemala's Interior Minister said on Thursday.
headline_main: U.S. Asylum Seekers Sent to Guatemala Preferring to Return to Home Countries
headline_print_headline: U.S. Asylum Seekers Sent to Guatemala Preferring to Return to Home Countries

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump is likely to nominate Hudson Institute CEO Kenneth Weinstein as ambassador to Japan, Jiji Press reported on Friday.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump is likely to nominate Hudson Institute CEO Kenneth Weinstein as ambassador to Japan, Jiji Press reported on Friday.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — U.S. President Donald Trump is likely to nominate Hudson Institute CEO Kenneth Weinstein as ambassador to Japan, Jiji Press reported on Friday.
headline_main: Trump Likely to Tap Hudson Institute's Weinstein for Ambassador to Japan: Jiji
headline_print_headline: Trump Likely to Tap Hudson Institute's Weinstein for Ambassador to Japan: Jiji

abstract: As the House moves toward what even he says is an inevitable vote to impeach him for high crimes and misdemeanors, President Trump toggles between self-pity and combativeness.
snippet: As the House moves toward what even he says is an inevitable vote to impeach him for high crimes and misdemeanors, President Trump toggles between self-pity and combativeness.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Under pressure over his possible impeachment, President Richard M. Nixon supposedly talked to the paintings in the White House. President Bill Clinton absently toyed with his old campaign buttons. President Trump punches out Twitter messages in the lonely midnight hour.

abstract: There's a campaign going on in  Washington  that even the most garrulous members of Congress aren't eager to talk about: to be part of a team of uncertain size, with a risky mission, to be named by a leader who isn't talking about what she's looking for or when she'll decide.
snippet: There's a campaign going on in  Washington  that even the most garrulous members of Congress aren't eager to talk about: to be part of a team of uncertain size, with a risky mission, to be named by a leader who isn't talking about what she's looki...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — There's a campaign going on in Washington that even the most garrulous members of Congress aren't eager to talk about: to be part of a team of uncertain size, with a risky mission, to be named by a leader who isn't talking about what she's looking for or when she'll decide.

abstract: The job pays up to 50,000 pounds a year (about $67,000), with weekends off and free lunch, according to Buckingham Palace.
snippet: The job pays up to 50,000 pounds a year (about $67,000), with weekends off and free lunch, according to Buckingham Palace.
lead_paragraph: It’s a job title you might expect to find at a media powerhouse or Silicon Valley start-up: head of digital engagement. The annual pay could be as much as 50,000 pounds, roughly $67,000. Oh, and there’s free lunch.
